  "summary": "Kougetsu Joushou confronts Daya=Hana=Anna-Stasia, revealing her true identity as a Russian princess of the Romanov bloodline. He explains that she killed the composer Medvedev because he knew of her existence. Driven by a desire to hide her assimilation into Japanese culture and prevent her lineage from being viewed as \"degenerate,\" she planned a massacre of the Kuragin family after economic liberalization reforms threatened to resurface Medvedev's work, \"Imakagami,\" and expose her secret.\n\nKougetsu reveals that he is the biological grandson of Anna-Stasia and the twin brother of McArthur (Ryuujin Raijou). He explains that his mother, Tomiko Akiyoshi, was a twin who secretly gave birth to him to protect his identity. To prove his lineage, he presents a gold cross and a talisman left by his mother. He clarifies that his intention in marrying Yuzu—Medvedev's great-granddaughter—is not for the Higuchi family fortune, but out of love, despite having the legal standing to claim the inheritance himself.\n\nKougetsu delivers a final psychological blow, labeling Anna-Stasia a \"failure\" and a \"puppet\" rather than a god or monarch. He accuses her of being a disgrace to the Romanov name and tells her not to resist him, as it would bring shame to her descendants. After delivering this revenge for his mother's death, Kougetsu leaves the location, predicting that the broken Anna-Stasia will likely take her own life rather than lose her remaining dignity.",
